text: <@U33EGB4TX> Do you have any thoughts on the call to ban Hogaak from Modern?
Something from that deck is probably going to get the ax I'm sure
Do you think that takes the heat off Faithless Looting or does that get the ax too?
It might be bridge, that would be my though process as that's what makes the deck go from aggro to combo
I don't think so, looting gives so many other decks life
Without it Dredge gets very different and much less powerful, phoenix gets significantly worse once it has to play tormenting voice and other worse versions
I saw one of those "change my mind" memes the other day that said "Faithless Looting is Ancestral Recall for Modern: Change my mind" and it gave me a chuckle.

It's the same reason stirrings is around at this point too. I think WotC hasn't axed it because it's powering so many different decks like tron, affinity, amulet etc. They've shown they'd rather ban the payoff cards or the more narrow engines like KCI than the broad ones
That's probably the more conservative and appropriate approach.
Yea, I don't hate that either
They're trying to manage the format, not upend it.
The card selection at a cost w/ stirrings is narrow unlike Ponder for example where it's seeing whatever 4 cards you want, where stirrings has to be strictly colorless
In the decks that play stirrings it's a 5'er, but that came at a deckbuilding cost. If you could snag a primetime w/ it then it would be a problem
True, but 5 for a single mana is a lot and obviously powerful in very powerful decks.
God that would be so amazing
From an outsiders perspective, altar of dementia seems like a card that if it doesn’t get the ax now, probably will in the future
Agreed, but the setback keeps it from any green deck from playing it
It’s just...so easy to break
Agreed.
Altar is another good one. If bridge from below is banned it goes from insane to just a very good engine
I imagine they wouldn’t be thrilled about banning so soon after putting it into modern
I think the deck w/o bridge and you have to rely on playing a more fair version would be easier to interact with and probably more fun
Yeah I feel like bridge gets it
Don't forget they also gave Modern [[Carrion Feeder]]

text: Yep, the sac outlets aren't quite as insane but still there
Cheap, free sac outlets are very much enabling tech.
It's easier game 1 to interact w/ a creature than an artifact though
Indeed
It's just in the decks that want the one, they probably want the other.
For the sheer density of that effect.
I think it's 70/30 bridge to altar being the problem
and the fact carrion gets bigger for each sack is relevant.

Not that altar isn't a problem, but if you're spending a mana to recur gravecrawler and need lands to recur bloodghast, it's much more manageable than getting free zombies to crank out and mill the shit out of people. The zombies from bridge turn the death of 1 creature into the death of 2 or 3 for milling purposes, which makes hogaak all the faster
[[spawning pit]] has been modern legal but sees no play that I know of, so just being a free sac outlet alone doesn't do it.

text: Bridge is very much a problem card.
The free recursion and incidental recursion from bridge has been what breaks the parity in every game I've seen with that deck
Games without bridge are still good, but it's not "holy fuck..." good
Right, the milling part is just synergistic with the rest of what the deck is trying to do
And it can be offensive if necessary.

Late to the party, but I feel like Altar of Dementia is the real issue.
